VERDICT: BEST SIGNAL YET, mechanism VALIDATED, gate still FAILS.
  * Diagonal dominance 2/3 (q1+q3) — the MONOTONIC LADDER Yes/No 0/3 -> first-tok Δcont 1/3
    -> multi-tok Δcont 2/3 confirms the depth diagnosis: relevance lives in the payload
    tokens (positions 3-8), not the boilerplate. Measuring there is correct.
  * GATE FAILS on the absolute threshold: min(matched)=-0.44 << max(foreign)=+5.11. Foreign
    queries throw confident ΔLL spikes (q5 dp4a->wiki +1.16; q9 sourdough->headlam +4.59;
    q8 France pins ALL THREE ~+4.5). ROOT CAUSE: "memory changed my answer" != "memory was
    relevant" — injecting an off-topic episode can still perturb an off-topic continuation,
    so a large +ΔLL is necessary but NOT sufficient for relevance.
  * q2 miss: lobster query, the matched lobster episode is mid (0.13) — the 12B's lobster
    continuation is generic enough that the episode adds little surprise vs zeroed.

NEXT (the orthogonal-consensus sieve, now with two GOOD signals): the v5 sieve failed because
its members (geom/learned/thermo) were correlated-bad. We now have TWO ~2/3 ORTHOGONAL signals:
q·K (Stage-1 GEOMETRIC relevance) and multi-tok ΔLL (Stage-2 GENERATIVE relevance). A foreign
ΔLL spike (q5/q9) is unlikely to coincide with a q·K top-rank for the same episode. Gate =
fire iff BOTH rank the SAME episode top AND each clears its own telemetry-pinned threshold.
This is the principled two-stage retrieve-and-verify the campaign pointed at, finally with two
signals worth intersecting. M_target=42 budget = the safety floor under it.

